panels.description: Numbers of GitHub events in all repositories hourly

targets.rawSql:
select
  time,
  value as "Number of GitHub events hourly"
from
  sevents_h
where
  $__timeFilter(time)
order by
  time

panels.title: Hourly [[full_name]] activity on GitHub

options.content:
Thanks for visiting the community dashboard for the [Kubernetes project](https://kubernetes.io/).

Before using any of the graphs, please check-out [the readme](https://github.com/cncf/devstats/blob/master/README_K8s.md) for additional context.

Please report any bugs by opening an issue on [the devstats repository](https://github.com/cncf/devstats/issues).

panels.title: Community sizing and health assessment dashboards

current.text:
Kubernetes Home dashboard

Links:

  • Postgres SQL file, database dumps.
  • TSDB series definition (search for name: GitHub activity).
  • Grafana dashboard JSON.
  • Developer documentation.
  • Direct link.

Description

  • First we're displaying links to all CNCF projects defined.
  • Next we're showing current project's hourly activity - this is the number of all GitHub events that happened for Kubernetes project hourly.
  • This also includes bots activity (most other dashboards skip bot activity).
  • Next we're showing HTML panel that shows all CNCF projects icons and links.
  • Next there is a dashboard that shows a list of all dashboards defined for Kubernetes project.
